n.org/pers-100275 Edmund Husserl on the Open Commons of Phenomenology]. Complete bibliography and links to all German texts, including ''Husserliana'' vols. I\u2013XXVIII\n\n{{continental philosophy}}\n{{Existentialism}}\n{{philosophy of mind}}\n{{Platonists}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Husserl, Edmund}}\n[[Category:Edmund Husserl| ]]\n[[Category:1859 births]]\n[[Category:1938 deaths]]\n[[Category:19th-century Austrian male writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century Austrian writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century German philosophers]]\n[[Category:19th-century German writers]]\n[[Category:19th-century philosophers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Austrian male writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century Austrian writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century German philosophers]]\n[[Category:20th-century German writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century philosophers]]\n[[Category:Austrian philosophers]]\n[[Category:Continental philosophers]]\n[[Category:Converts to Lutheranism from Judaism]]\n[[Category:Descartes scholars]]\n[[Category:Epistemologists]]\n[[Category:Existentialists]]\n[[Category:Founders of philosophical traditions]]\n[[Category:German Jews]]\n[[Category:German logicians]]\n[[Category:German Lutherans]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n[[Category:German philosophers]]\n[[Category:History of ideas]]\n[[Category:History of logic]]\n[[Category:History of mathematics]]\n[[Category:History of philosophy]]\n[[Category:Humboldt University of Berlin alumni]]\n[[Category:Leipzig University alumni]]\n[[Category:Lutheran philosophers]]\n[[Category:Jewish philosophers]]\n[[Category:Martin Luther University of Halle-Wittenberg alumni]]\n[[Category:Metaphysicians]]\n[[Category:Ontologists]]\n[[Category:People from Prost\u011bjov]]\n[[Category:People from the Margraviate of Moravia]]\n[[Category:Phenomenologists]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of culture]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of education]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of language]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of logic]]\n[[Category:Philosophers of mat